<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-38-0914 </DOCNO><TEXT>Using electron microscopy, synapses of different structures of the ratend brain related to cognitive and motor acts (sensorimotor cortex, caudatenucleus) as well as memory and behavior (hippocampus) were examined.Rats were exposed to ionizing radiation, superhigh frequency, hypoxia,hyperoxia, vibration and acceleration (applied separately or in combination)which have been traditionally in the focus of space and aviation medicine.Brain internuronal junctions were found to be very sensitive to the aboveeffects, particularly ionizing radiation and hypoxia. Conversely, synapseswere shown to be highly resistant to short-term hyperoxia and electromagneticradiation. When combined effects were used, response of interneuronaljunctions depended on the irradiation dose and order of application ofradiation and other flight factors.</TEXT></DOC>